{"article_id":"C40bRYy4AX4wLg2L","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"For more than three years , Republicans have engaged each other in a heated debate","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"over whether the proper response to the passage of the Affordable Care Act is to repeal it","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"and replace it with something else ,","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"or to just repeal it","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"and return to the pre-Obamacare status quo .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"In effect , their actual position is the latter .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"They 've voted to repeal the law over and over again ,","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"but have never reached a consensus on a single plan","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"to replace it .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"And at times during the long lead-up to Obamacare 's big launch , that failure has been a liability for them .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"It 's damaged their credibility as healthcare reform critics with the press and the public alike .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"The old system sucked !","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Why should we go back to it ?","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"Given how troubled the Obamacare rollout has been ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"you might think","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"that Republicans are kicking themselves particularly hard right now","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"for not settling on a `` GOP healthcare plan . ''","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"What better time","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"to argue for repeal","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"than under circumstances like these ?","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"But you 'd be wrong .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"If anything , they 're incredibly relieved .","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"Because a `` replace '' plan would neutralize what has proved to be one of their best , and relatedly most disingenuous , lines of attack against the law","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"since it passed in 2010 .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"We know","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"the outrage","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Republicans are expressing on behalf of people","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"receiving cancellation notices from their individual market insurance plans","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"is phony","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"because it 's obviously phony .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"They do n't have any particular interest","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"in ameliorating this phenomenon","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"short of repealing or destroying the rest of the law .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"And its effectiveness as a talking point hinges on never acknowledging","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"that Obamacare has helped anybody .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"But the most revealing tell ,","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"identified here by the New Republic 's Jonathan Cohn ,","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"is that all of the healthcare reform plans","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Republicans support","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"would disrupt the insurance market much more dramatically","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"than the Affordable Care Act does .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Republicans ca n't achieve consensus on a plan","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"to replace Obamacare ,","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"but they all basically agree","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"that very few people should be allowed to keep the insurance plans","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"they have right now .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Jonathan explains","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"how almost all GOP plans would kick millions of people off of Medicaid ,","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"and inflict adverse selection on the employer-sponsored insurance market","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"by creating a huge incentive","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"for healthy workers to abandon their group plans for individual ones .","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"The ensuing death spiral would result in more cancellation notices and `` rate shock ''","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"than we 're seeing now by an order of magnitude ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"but without the safety net of the Affordable Care Act 's exchanges","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"to catch people .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"The National Review 's Ramesh Ponnuru 's solution to this problem is to rip the band-aid off slowly .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Whereas Obamacare creates an immediate disruption for a relatively small group of individual policyholders ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"Republicans should create a slow , steady disruption for tens of millions more .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Other smart conservatives","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"-- which is to say ,","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"policy wonks","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"without much cachet on Capitol Hill --","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"would replace all insurance with subsidized catastrophic coverage and tax-preferred health savings accounts .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"Nobody with private insurance or Medicaid would get to keep what they have ,","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"no matter how much they like it .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"I 'd add another .","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"Nearly all Republicans support eliminating traditional Medicare for future retirees , and replacing it with a plan","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"that looks","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"( ironically )","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"a lot like Obamacare .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"The sales pitch version of the plan is that Republicans want to keep the promise","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"the country made to current retirees and people","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"nearing retirement ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"but radically overhaul it for the young and middle-aged .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Over time , single-payer Medicare would be phased out .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"But","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"as nearly every healthcare expert will tell you ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"the phase-out would be massively disruptive .","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"As the program 's beneficiaries aged","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"and dwindled in number ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"it would become unsustainable very quickly .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"Without scale ,","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"the government would lose its purchasing power ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"and would either have to fork over tons of money","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"to motivate providers to care for beneficiaries","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"-- a bailout --","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"or watch providers abandon the program en masse ,","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"leaving the country 's oldest , sickest people little choice","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"but to enter the private insurance market .","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"Republicans are treating Obama 's `` if you like your plan","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"you can keep it '' pitch as the noble lie","depth":5},{"id":91,"text":"from which all of the apocalyptic consequences of the Affordable Care Act will ultimately spring .","depth":4},{"id":92,"text":"The original swindle .","depth":4},{"id":93,"text":"But the focus-grouped deception","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"they hope to perpetrate against seniors","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"is far more egregious .","depth":5},{"id":96,"text":"If a consensus GOP plan existed today ,","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"Republicans would have to square their outpouring of sympathy for beleaguered young policyholders with the radical intent of their own vision .","depth":6},{"id":98,"text":"I imagine","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"they","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"-- like Obama ! --","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"would n't be forthright about the consequences .","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"The truth is ,","depth":5},{"id":103,"text":"that plan would fail on the floor of the House either way .","depth":5},{"id":104,"text":"Precisely because it 's so radical ,","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"I strongly doubt","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"there will ever be a political constituency for it .","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"Even if Republicans someday control the government again .","depth":6},{"id":108,"text":"( Remember the last time","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"they controlled the government","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"and ruptured the healthcare system ?","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"Me neither . )","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"But","depth":5},{"id":113,"text":"if someday they do ,","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"and charge ahead with a plan","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"that contains elements like these ,","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"the consequences and the political fallout will make the great cancellation row of 2013 look like a website glitch .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":233,"left":205,"right":232,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":205,"left":129,"right":204,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":122,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":121,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":121,"left":0,"right":120,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":118,"right":119,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":118,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":119,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":128,"left":6,"right":127,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":127,"left":123,"right":126,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":9,"right":125,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":10,"right":124,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":204,"left":150,"right":203,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":150,"left":137,"right":149,"relation":"expl